# Blackboard LMS MCP Server

A [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/) (MCP) server that gives AI agents tools to interact with the Blackboard LMS Learning Management System.

Generated by `blackboard-lms-sdk-generator` v{{metadata.generatorVersion}} from spec version {{metadata.specVersion}}.

## Quick Start

### Install

```bash
pip install blackboard-lms-mcp
```

### Configure

Set the required environment variables:

```bash
export BLACKBOARD_BASE_URL="https://your-institution.blackboard.com"
export BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_ID="your-application-key"
export BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_SECRET="your-application-secret"
```

### Run with Claude Desktop

Add to your Claude Desktop config (`~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "blackboard-lms": {
      "command": "blackboard-lms-mcp",
      "env": {
        "BLACKBOARD_BASE_URL": "https://your-institution.blackboard.com",
        "BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_ID": "your-application-key",
        "BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_SECRET": "your-application-secret"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Run with HTTP Transport

For networked access:

```bash
MCP_TRANSPORT=streamable-http MCP_HTTP_PORT=8000 blackboard-lms-mcp
```

