## Authentication

The server supports three authentication modes:

### Client Credentials (Two-Legged OAuth)

For server-to-server integrations. Set `BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_ID` and `BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_SECRET`. The server automatically obtains and refreshes tokens.

### Pre-obtained Token

For testing or external token management. Set `BLACKBOARD_API_TOKEN` instead of client credentials.

### Authorization Code + PKCE (Three-Legged OAuth)

For user-delegated access. Set `BLACKBOARD_REDIRECT_URI` to enable OAuth tools (`learn_auth_get_login_url`, `learn_auth_exchange_code`, `learn_auth_status`). The AI agent can then drive the authorization flow to act on behalf of a specific user.

```bash
export BLACKBOARD_BASE_URL="https://your-institution.blackboard.com"
export BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_ID="your-application-key"
export BLACKBOARD_CLIENT_SECRET="your-application-secret"
export BLACKBOARD_REDIRECT_URI="https://your-app.com/auth/callback"
```

For a complete guide covering all authentication methods, token lifecycle, and security best practices, see the **[Authentication Guide](docs/authentication.md)**.

